reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great lamp / great service
reviews.reviewText: I needed a lamp to put on a dresser to give more light in my craft room. I wanted something small but which threw a lot of light. This lamp almost does the trick. It's a lovely little light and the 3-way bulb is pretty bright, but not quite enough for my needs. However, the lamp came with a card inside that said if the bulb wasn't bright enough, they'd send a brighter one (!) if requested. I emailed the compny and got a very quick response saying they had shipped a new bulb and even sent a copy of the shipping label with the tracking number (5 stars+ for customer service!!!). The touch feature works nicely (soft light at first touch and brighter for each of 2 more taps, then touch to turn off. The simulated wood base is very pretty and the lamp is well made with an attractive, quality shade. Just one note: follow the instructions for putting the shade on. I tried doing it without reading at first and the shade was very wobbly. When I followed the easy instructions, it was very stable and looked great. I probably won't need to use the charging ports or the A/C plug in the base much, but they are unintrusive and a nice-to-have, if needed. I'll update regarding the new bulb when it arrives. I've already received a USPS notification that it will arrive in 2 days (it's currently the weekend) - so, again, 5 stars+ for GREAT service from this company!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased two of these lamps for my bedroom and they are amazing! The ability to charge my phone on it has saved space on my night table. The bulbs are on a dimmer and look fantastic. Quality is better than I expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Terrific, useful, attractive lamp
reviews.reviewText: This lamp is very pretty, sturdy, and versatile. In the wood-look base (it’s actually metal) with linen shade it is perfect with every decor. Love the touch switch, which works to set the bulb (included) to 3 brightness levels with just a tap of your finger on the base or neck of the lamp. Bulb stays cool even if it’s on for hours. The lamp came packaged carefully and unboxing it and performing the minimal assembly is very simple. The company will ship a free extra bulb if you prefer one of three choices they offer for a cooler brightness. Instructions to obtain another free bulb are included with the assembly booklet.I bought this lamp to be a bedside light in my small guest bedroom. It lights more than sufficiently for a reading light and has a warm illumination at all 3 levels. The bulb is dimmable and will work with a smart outlet, too. The base of the lamp solves the need to provide a guest with a phone or tablet charging outlet. A USB-A and a USB-C port are built right into the base. Either port will take an appropriate charger cable. There is also a fully functional 110v AC outlet in the lamp base. I tested all 3 receptacles and they all work perfectly. Lights, charging ports and an electric outlet all in one pretty lamp. Irresistible value.The lamp comes with a lifetime guarantee and customer service is friendly and helpful. The lamp is flawless. Pick the base & shade you like best and order it. You’ll find it useful and of very good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice lamp, great features
reviews.reviewText: The lamp is great. The bulb that is included provides nice light but could be brighter. I emailed customer service for a brighter bulb and the response was immediate and I had another bulb within a week. The bulb is a bit brighter and light is whiter and less soft than the original bulb, but seems better for reading. The USB ports and touch feature to turn on/off are handy and functional. Very good purchase overall. Impressed by the next level customer service.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bedside lamp
reviews.reviewText: We like this for its soft look on and off, not overpowering. Light given off is soft and just enough. I’ve seen other reviews that talk about bulb being too dim, and ours came with a factory offer for a free replacement brighter bulb. I like the light given off now even with the black shade, so no brighter not needed by us. Charger plugs on base are handy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sleek, stylish, user-friendly
reviews.reviewText: I needed a lamp to supplement the faint light available during gloomy overcast days during the daytime and to allow for my Christmas lights to remain on while working at my desk at night (without having to turn on overhead lighting). This was a great cost-efficient solution that also complements the minimalist decor of my room and allows me to charge my devices. The assembly is quick and tool-less, and the touch-activation means no fiddling with switches or knobs. The bulb is, as others have commented, a bit faint, so I will take up the company on its offer to request a brighter one, free of charge.

reviews.reviewText: Both lamps arrived undamaged. The lightbulb is cleverly and securely attached to the stem of the lamp.I’m using them on my desk at work that was dimly lit.They put out a good amount of light which is warm and natural. The incandescent bulbs are great, and good for the eyes!
